notesStmt.note: This square-format manuscript is volume 2, containing chapters 19-114 (Surat Maryam through Sūrat al-nās), of an illuminated two-volume Qur'an produced in Sub-Saharan (West) Africa in the thirteenth century AH / nineteenth CE. The text is written in Sūdānī script in dark brown ink with vocalization in red on loose leaves. Chapter headings are in reddish-brown ink. Three yellow dots outlined in red arranged in a triangular form separate verses. Polychrome circular medallions as well as square and rectangular devices in a variety of patterns and colors mark textual divisions. The leaves of the text are organized between two decorated boards with geometric compositions. The pages and boards are housed in a leather pouch (satchel).

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Arabic.

support.p: Cream European laid paper, probably Italian (fragments of tre lune watermark visible)

collation.p: On versosLoose leaves stacked between boards

handDesc.handNote: Written in a Sūdānī hand in dark brown ink with vocalization in red

decoDesc.decoNote: Chapter headings in reddish-brown ink accompanied by marginal geometric designs; three yellow dots outlined in triangular form as verse markers; polychrome circular medallions as well as square and rectangular devices in a variety of patterns and colors as textual divisions of sixty (ḥizb), thirty (juzʾ), and seven (subʿ) sections

decoNote.title: Right side of a double-page frontispiece with geometrical design
decoNote.note: This is the right side of a double-page frontispiece in the form of a square with geometrical design in the center.

decoNote.title: Left side of a double-page frontispiece with geometrical design
decoNote.note: This is the left side of a double-page frontispiece in the form of a square with geometrical design in the center.

decoNote.title: Text page with chapter heading for chapter 19
decoNote.note: This text page has the chapter heading for chapter 19 (Surat Maryam) written in reddish brown ink, indicating title, number of verses, and place of revelation as Mecca.

decoNote.title: Chapter heading for chapter 20
decoNote.note: Chapter heading; marker for textual division
This text page has the chapter heading for chapter 20 (Sūrat Ṭā Hā) written in reddish-brown ink. In the margin is a circular medallion marking the division of the text into sixty sections (ḥizb).

decoNote.title: Inside of the lower board
decoNote.note: The inside of this lower board is decorated with a star-shaped geometric design. The loose leaves of this Qur'an are sandwiched between this board and the upper board. It is common for Qur’ans from Muslim sub-Saharan Africa to assume this format.

decoNote.title: Leather pouch (satchel)
decoNote.note: The loose leaves and boards of this Qur'an are protected within a leather pouch (satchel) with a flap and thong on the outside.

binding.p: Two loose boards decorated on both sides with geometric designs and fastened with leather thongs; leaves and boards protected within a leather pouch (satchel) with flap and thong on the outside
